</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[714,1247,352,532]" pageId="17" pageNumber="72">
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[1001,1180,352,379]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Disperis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="17" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hildebrandtii">
<emphasis box="[1001,1180,352,379]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="72">D. hildebrandtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its habit. It is readily distinguished by the terminal appendage of its lip which is stalked not sessile and by the indumentum of that appendage which lacks the vesicular hairs that are characteristic of 
<taxonomicName box="[714,885,505,532]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Disperis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="17" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hildebrandtii">
<emphasis box="[714,885,505,532]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="72">D. hildebrandtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
